Monospaced fonts are only added if they can be used in kitty. To check:

fc-list : family spacing | grep spacing | grep -Po '^[^:,]+' | sort -u

Mono: Source Code Pro
Sans: IBM Plex Sans (firefox, mpv osd)
Serif: IBM Plex Serif (firefox)

To update:
wget -c https://github.com/IBM/plex/raw/master/IBM-Plex-Sans/fonts/complete/otf/IBMPlexSans-Regular.otf https://github.com/IBM/plex/raw/master/IBM-Plex-Serif/fonts/complete/otf/IBMPlexSerif-Regular.otf https://github.com/mozilla/Fira/raw/master/otf/FiraMono-Regular.otf https://github.com/googlefonts/silkscreen/raw/main/fonts/otf/Silkscreen-Regular.otf https://github.com/adobe-fonts/source-code-pro/raw/release/OTF/SourceCodePro-Regular.otf

Where are fonts declared?

	~/.Xresources
	~/.config/dunst/dunstrc
	~/.config/gtk-3.0/settings.ini
	~/.config/kitty/kitty.conf
	~/.config/mpv/mpv.conf
	~/.config/rofi/config.rasi
	~/.mozilla/firefox/4clnophl.default/user.js
	~/dwm/config.h
